theorem nonempty_of_nonempty_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    (interior (closure (A : Set X))).Nonempty → (A : Set X).Nonempty := by
  intro hInt
  by_contra hA
  -- `hA` says that `A` is empty.
  have hAeq : (A : Set X) = ∅ := Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty.mp hA
  -- Hence `interior (closure A)` is also empty.
  have hIntEq : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
    simpa [hAeq, closure_empty] using interior_empty
  -- This contradicts the assumed non‐emptiness of `interior (closure A)`.
  have : (∅ : Set X).Nonempty := by
    simpa [hIntEq] using hInt
  exact this.elim

theorem P1_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P1 (∅ : Set X) := by
  simpa using (Topology.empty_has_all_Ps (X := X)).1
